(2759, 88, 'locations__the_content', '<p class="p1">Dishoom literally means \'bang\' (or to be more exact, the sound a bullet makes when it flies through the air) and the way this all day cafe has exploded onto the London scene,  the names sees very apt.</p>\r\n<p class="p1">Back when Bombay, was still Bombay, their local all day cafes were the centre of society, they would host everything from important meetings, family celebrations or casual meets, it is this relaxed social eating culture that has won the hearts of our city. It\'s all day serving of a wide range of small authentic dishes suits the busy London lifestyle and with retro decor and a strong cocktail menu, it seems people can\'t get enough of it with it buzzing with diners every night of the week. Unfortunately you are unable to reserve a table, so be prepared queue and wait for a table however the bar area is ideal for pre-drinks to take the edge of the hold-up.</p>\r\n<p class="p1"></p>'),
