(2930, 71, 'locations__the_content', 'Like many things that used to be a piss covered hole in the ground, you’ll find the Attendant in Shoreditch. Its main claim to fame is that it used to be a public urinal, but don’t worry, no one in here will say “freshen up” to you as you wash your hands. Instead, you’ll find a lovely range of café snacks and excellent coffee supplied by indie roasters, <a href="http://www.caravanonexmouth.co.uk/roastery/about">Caravan</a>. They have a great range of baked treats too, though we already checked and, no: they don’t sell anything called the Urinal Cake.'),
