(3003, 83, 'locations__the_content', 'New Orleans comes to London! Even if you don\'t like the taste of bourbon, you will feel like you want to order one because this place feels so bloody authentic!\r\n\r\nThey\'ve really nailed the southern vibe here, the decor is raw and rugged, there\'s even a parked trailer at the back that you can hire for private parties and while they have live music most nights, even without the bands, the music is loud and brash with a blend of rock \'n\' roll, blues and honky tonk - which just adds to the atmosphere!\r\n\r\nWhile this bar is really cool, the real winning factor of the Blues Kitchen is the food! Mouthwatering barbecue dishes of ribs and chicken wings, with classic southern sides corn-bread, crunchy \'slaw and burnt end brisket beans - a winning combo!'),
