(3075, 95, 'locations__the_content', '[embed]https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=UKUG1itg4Eo[/embed]\r\n\r\nWhat began as a pop up barbecue, HotBox is now firmly established with a permanent residency but they have cleverly managed to keep their original street vibe. Shuffle in along the wooden benches and admire menu which mixes your typical barbecue favourites with Asian influences creating smoked delights, like sausages and pulled pork to their show-stopping beef rib, cooked and smoked for 8 hours delivering the most mouthwatering flavour!\r\n\r\nThe venue encourages a community feel with guest often getting involved in a bit of banter and a lot of food envy so it\'s great for group meets. Take your cool artistic friends to the downstairs bar (thoughtfully named \'46 &amp; mercy\') who will love the rumoured association with Banksy\'s print studio and will oogle the amazing art pieces from the likes of Robbo and Pure Evil.\r\n<p class="p1"> this super cool venue is filled with lively Londoners who want to enjoy top notch BBQ food. Their drinks menu is inspired by the food and offers a host of fun bourbon based cocktails.</p>\r\n<p class="p1">The staff at Hot box are some of the nicest you will come across and with a buzzing atmosphere, and delicious grub – this restaurant it hot hot hot.</p>'),
(3076, 95, '_locations__the_content', 'field_56221eea97ca0'),
(3077, 95, 'maplist_description', 'A street style barbecue house serving mouthwatering serving some of the best smoked delights in the capital, from ribs to pulled port and sausages this super cool venue.'),
