(3510, 295, 'locations__the_content', 'The grown-up way to watch a movie nowadays is with a beer and a comfy sofa at a quirky independent screening venue (most people wouldn\'t be seen dead at an Odeon)! So if you are off to see the latest block buster - or something more arty - Rich Mix, situated between Shoreditch and Bethnal Green, is pretty perfect.\r\n\r\nAs a charity and social enterprise Rich Mix tries to deliver a broad artistic programme to suit all cultures and backgrounds, and they achieve this seamlessly with everything from live music, film, dance, theatre and comedy. With 5 floors and three cinema screens showing both mainstream and independent films, you can sneak into see the latest geeky trilogy or shameless disney film without anyone batting an eye lid.'),
