(4007, 97, 'locations__the_content', '[embed]https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=lRi3PmXuJ5I[/embed]\r\n<p class="p1">There was a distinct point when Korean food became trendy, and that was probably the day that JinJuu opened. Not only is Korean food one of the healthiest cuisines in the world it is also truly scrumptious! Swiftly overtaking as a favourite choice amongst Londoners, JinJuu is a total hit - with casual dining concepts in a glossy Carnaby Street location.</p>\r\n<p class="p1">The highlight for many is their “Anju” selection – which refers to food that you eat while you drink (what\'s not to love) so picture a Korean/Asian fusion of tacos and sliders over a few classes of chilled white wine (is your mouth watering yet?)</p>\r\n<p class="p1">While the food hits the spot, your eyes can devour the cool graffiti artwork and your ears will be treated to resident DJs playing vibrant tunes.</p>'),
