(6020, 392, 'locations__the_content', 'Looking for a puuuuuuufect escape from the working week? This might be just the place.\r\n\r\nMost of busy Londoners give up the luxury of having a pet when they join the 9-5 (more like 8-7 these days) rat race in the city.  Working long, often unsociable hours and strict tenancy rules often mean there are no fluffy faces waiting at the door to greet you on your return from a stressful day (unless you have a bearded flat mate.)\r\n\r\nLady Dinah\'s Emporium might just be the answer to your pet-less prayers! Lined with comfy sofas and bookcases and kitsch decor, you\'ll feel like your at you\'ve stopped at your Nan\'s house and as you sit down to relax, the resident cats will strut their stuff around the place, come over to say hello and have a cuddle with the cat loving guests.\r\n\r\nThey serve more than just coffee and cakes, there is a range of breakfast and snack options, and their Afternoon Teas are really popular - but book ahead to avoid disappointment!\r\n\r\n&nbsp;'),
