(6107, 393, 'locations__the_content', 'Being located in the basement of an old-style boozer gives 5cc a unique atmosphere. When that boozer is the Singer Tavern, named for the former occupants, Singer Corporation, it all just gets sew much cooler. (We hope these puns have you in stitches.) A word to the wise though, only come here if you love gin, because that’s what they do best, though admittedly, not exclusively. With burnished bars, leather seats and forgivingly dim lighting, 5CC is a genuine slice of cool in London’s most over-hyped area\r\n\r\n[embed]https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=56QHHzImzO0[/embed]'),
