(6368, 396, 'locations__the_content', '<p class="p2">Cosrica is one of London’s most important club venues, but it was originally meant to be a gallery space. This explains two things: its old name, Corsica Arts Club, and why the gents only has two cubicles despite the club having a capacity of 500.</p>\r\n<p class="p2">Corsica Studios is famous for its late 6am weekend license and 24-hour events that stretch all the way through to Sunday nights. Elephant &amp; Castle’s most famous institution, Corsica is a favourite hangout for South London icons like King Krule and Jamie XX, and regularly attracts the world’s best DJs to its modest under-the-arches location.</p>\r\n<p class="p2"></p>'),
