(6542, 398, 'locations__the_content', '<p class="p1">One of Shoreditch’s older, more genuine institutions, by day The Book Club is a white-tiled kitchen, boozer and creative hangout. At night, the stairs to the basement open up a low-ceiling world of famous DJs, cool decorations and New York-style cool.</p>\r\n<p class="p1">The fun to be had here is evenly split between full on party and arty soiree. The Book Club has championed a ‘Thinking &amp; Drinking’ approach to fun in the city that makes walking in to find a terrarium-making workshop just as likely as passing by and hearing 70s disco classics seeping up from below the streets. There’s also a legendary ping pong table in the back room.</p>'),
