(6629, 399, 'locations__the_content', 'Is Salt Yard’s West End sister: a little tartier, a little more expensive and a lot more popular with tourists. This is tapas heaven, with both Italian and Spanish on the menu, and let me tell you now – it’s damn fancy. How fancy? Escabeche of partridge fancy. Venison haunch with pumpkin purée fancy. Let’s just say Iggy Azealia would feel a bit plain sat in here.\r\n\r\nAway from the table you can enjoy a fantastic range of sherries (see? Fancy!), captivating interior design and an unbelievable Covent Garden location. The perfect beginning or end to a night at the opera.'),
