(6717, 400, 'locations__the_content', '<p class="p2">8 Hoxton Square brings a touch of class to the noisy, debauched geometric-misnomer that is Hoxton Square. There’s nothing square about the bars surrounding this small park, nor about number 8 itself. Here you can try some seriously sophisticated food that picks and chooses from all over Europe: a staunchly English venison pie and mash, a deliciously Byzantine sea bass with spiced cauliflower, yoghurt and coriander.</p>\r\n<p class="p2">Although the big mains are pricier than the local competition, they’re top notch. What’s really impressive though is their much cheaper breakfast/brunch selection and their divine smaller dishes which are served all day and make the perfect accompaniment to a bottle of wine and a good natter with a friend.</p>'),
