(11527, 631, 'locations__the_content', 'Graphic is a bar that has 305 different bottles of gin on its shelves. That’s one hell of a collection if you ever fancy going on the juniper joyride of a lifetime. Open a satisfyingly simple noon-midnight, Monday-Saturday, Graphic’s drinks menu would itself make a horrid cocktail because it’s 65% gin, with token beers and wines for those who really were dragged along.\r\n\r\nThere’s a scant selection of bar snacks but a great selection of, that most nebulous term, urban art. This mix of hard, hard alcohol, urban art and a Golden Square location make Graphic the definitive Soho Bar. Watch out for Francis Bacon’s ghost.'),
