(76, 1, '2015-10-09 17:32:05', '2015-10-09 17:32:05', '<p class="p1">Positioned on one of the most famous streets in London, this dress down barnyard is a refreshing dining experience. Packed with the capitals cool kids, Barnyard specialises in simple hearty grub.</p>\r\n<p class="p1">A friendly vibe, that is both affordable and fun – so whether you’re taking the kids along – or you want to relive your favourite childhood meals, you can tuck into sausage rolls, fry-ups and<span class="Apple-converted-space">  </span>bubble ’n’ squeak.;</p>\r\n<p class="p1">Those wanting a low calorie, organic goodness should avoid – this is gourmet junk food at its very best.</p>', 'Barnyard', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'barnyard', '', '', '2015-10-17 11:58:34', '2015-10-17 11:58:34', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8888/mct-wordpress/?post_type=maplist&#038;p=76', 0, 'maplist', '', 0),
(77, 1, '2015-10-09 17:34:17', '2015-10-09 17:34:17', '<p class="p1">Set up by two friends who had passion for decadent drinks and deserts, the Basement State is a Parisian styled bar with an intimate feel.</p>\r\n<p class="p1">One of the few destination in London where grown-ups can go for ice-cream, sample their<span class="Apple-converted-space">  </span>to-die-for<span class="Apple-converted-space">  </span>deserts, whether it be the Peanut Butter Jelly Times, or a white chocolate Hemispherical Dream.</p>\r\n<p class="p1">The sugar overload is even more satisfying when accompanied by a cocktail in this divine setting.</p>', 'Basement State', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'basement-state', '', '', '2015-12-11 14:49:20', '2015-12-11 14:49:20', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8888/mct-wordpress/?post_type=maplist&#038;p=77', 0, 'maplist', '', 0),
