(83, 1, '2015-10-09 18:07:38', '2015-10-09 18:07:38', '<p class="p1">The little sister of Blues Kitchen Camden, this is one of the coolest venues in East London!<span class="Apple-converted-space">  </span>A huge impressive building play host to this New Orleans inspired music hall. Feast on huge portions of Cajun comfort food<span class="Apple-converted-space"> </span>menu and sample of their classic bourbon inspired cocktails in a cosy booth. Live music kicks off around 9 pm with an eclectic mix from blues to swing and DJs play most night until 3am! There is even sometimes a bucking bronco that pops up for those feeling brave – but whether your in the saddle or not – this place is a party every night of the week.</p>', 'The Blues Kitchen', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'the-blues-kitchen', '', '', '2015-12-18 12:47:53', '2015-12-18 12:47:53', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8888/mct-wordpress/?post_type=maplist&#038;p=83', 0, 'maplist', '', 0),
(85, 1, '2015-10-09 18:15:00', '2015-10-09 18:15:00', '<p class="p1">Escape to wonderland with a trip to Calooh Calley. An indulgent cocktail bar nestled in Shoreditch where you are transported to the middle of a Lewis Carroll novel.<span class="Apple-converted-space">  </span>Fitted with its very own secret wardrobe and eccentric décor, every visitor will feel like a character in a story book.<span class="Apple-converted-space">  </span>Award winning cocktail menu, regularly updated by their talented<span class="Apple-converted-space">  </span>bartenders.</p>\r\n<p class="p1">Reserve a table or for a private area you can reserve your own quirky room.</p>\r\n<p class="p1">Whether you are a lover of literature or just enjoy a nice drink in a cool spot – Calooh Calley is always a hit.</p>', 'Calooh Calley', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'calooh-calley', '', '', '2015-12-18 12:23:37', '2015-12-18 12:23:37', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8888/mct-wordpress/?post_type=maplist&#038;p=85', 0, 'maplist', '', 0),
(87, 1, '2015-10-09 18:30:42', '2015-10-09 18:30:42', '<p class="p1">With a cool twist on the old fashioned chicken spots in the UK, \'Chicken Shop\' is the hot property in London. The Balham haunt is actually more than just chicken – aptly named ‘Chicken and Egg shop’. Serving the classic staple chicken menu plus incredible side dishes (the same as it’s sister restaurants in Kentish Town, Whitechapel<span class="Apple-converted-space">  </span>and Holborn) however this venue serves up breakfast too! So whether you want to tuck into eggs for breakfast or their famous marinated free-range birds<span class="Apple-converted-space">  </span>for dinner – the chicken and egg shop is simply spectacular.</p>', 'Chicken & Egg Shop', '', 'trash', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'chicken-egg-shop', '', '', '2015-12-11 14:35:46', '2015-12-11 14:35:46', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8888/mct-wordpress/?post_type=maplist&#038;p=87', 0, 'maplist', '', 0),
(88, 1, '2015-10-09 18:39:57', '2015-10-09 18:39:57', '<p class="p1">This bombay-style café has taken London by storm! Styled like the old post-colonial \'Irani cafés\' of Bombay, diners can enjoy the retro décor and array of authentic dishes. Londoners<span class="Apple-converted-space">  </span>are famous for their love of Indian food but this twist delivers something truly different. Start your day with a fun, modern takes on sub-continental street food, or meet friends in the evening for cocktails and sample menus.</p>\r\n<p class="p1">Bookings are<span class="Apple-converted-space"> </span>not accepted so be prepared for a potential queue, but it is most definitely worth the wait.</p>', 'Dishoom', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'dishoom', '', '', '2015-12-18 12:11:17', '2015-12-18 12:11:17', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8888/mct-wordpress/?post_type=maplist&#038;p=88', 0, 'maplist', '', 0),
(89, 1, '2015-10-09 18:43:54', '2015-10-09 18:43:54', '<p class="p1">Some bars and restaurants in London are just not enough to entertain the overactive mind of a creative which is why Drink Shop Do is a dream come true. This cafe by day, bar by night - enables you to drink and eat whilst embarking on some very fun tasks, from the more normal “Let’s get quizzical” quiz night, to "Pimp my shades" workshops!</p>\r\n<p class="p1">The eclectic all-day menu serves up delights from ham hock, quinoa salads and cheese and biscuits so it’s ideal for a light lunch or join them after your work day is done for bubbles, beers and cocktails for their amazing evening workshops.</p>', 'Drink Shop Do', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'drink-shop-do', '', '', '2015-12-11 14:35:24', '2015-12-11 14:35:24', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8888/mct-wordpress/?post_type=maplist&#038;p=89', 0, 'maplist', '', 0),
(90, 1, '2015-10-09 19:04:13', '2015-10-09 19:04:13', '<p class="p2">A small but perfectly formed restaurant with a truly "local" Mediterranean feel. Ducksoup has an extremely cosy décor and ambiance– so much so, that you can even select your own choice of vinyl to play while you eat. The menu changes almost daily, using the best season’s product offering an eclectic array of dishes. Imagine the best bits of Mediterranean tapas style dining, mixed with some classic British bite and middle Eastern twist – a recipe for success.</p>\r\n<p class="p2">In the centre of Soho – it is one of the few restaurants that doesn’t take itself too seriously just offers a great atmosphere perfect to unwind with friends.</p>', 'Ducksoup', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'ducksoup', '', '', '2015-12-16 17:46:48', '2015-12-16 17:46:48', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8888/mct-wordpress/?post_type=maplist&#038;p=90', 0, 'maplist', '', 0),
(91, 1, '2015-10-09 19:05:31', '2015-10-09 19:05:31', '<p class="p1">World famous restaurant chain Hakkasan is a Michelin Star award-winning Restaurant. This venue hidden in Soho offers modern Cantonese cuisine and a world-class drinks menu and an impressive 16 metre long bar!</p>\r\n<p class="p1">Stunning interio, with low lighting and delicious scents that fill everyone of your senses with Asian fusion.</p>\r\n<p class="p1">A most perfect setting for a special occasion whether it be celebrating the brief you have won or the promotion you have received. Its ultra-cool and sophisticated and the service is exemplary.</p>', 'Hakkasan', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'hakkasan', '', '', '2015-12-16 17:31:12', '2015-12-16 17:31:12', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8888/mct-wordpress/?post_type=maplist&#038;p=91', 0, 'maplist', '', 0),
(92, 1, '2015-10-09 19:07:32', '2015-10-09 19:07:32', '<p class="p1">World famous restaurant chain Hakkasan is a Michelin Star award-winning Restaurant. This venue hidden in Soho offers modern Cantonese cuisine and a world-class drinks menu and an impressive 16 metre long bar!</p>\n<p class="p1">Stunning interio, with low lighting and delicious scents that fill everyone of your senses with Asian fusion.</p>\n<p class="p1">A most perfect setting for a special occasion whether it be celebrating the brief you have won or the promotion you have received. Its ultra-cool and sophisticated and the service is exemplary.</p>', 'Hakkasan', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '91-autosave-v1', '', '', '2015-10-09 19:07:32', '2015-10-09 19:07:32', '', 91, 'http://localhost:8888/mct-wordpress/2015/10/09/91-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(93, 1, '2015-10-09 19:09:52', '2015-10-09 19:09:52', '<p class="p2">HIX is a classy British Bistro in the heart of Soho, serving a menu those changes weekly to keep diners on their toes. Enjoy their<span class="Apple-converted-space">  </span>signature British dishes in uber cool surroundings filled with a collection of neon art from celebrated British artists and a cool apothecary bar.</p>\r\n<p class="p2">Once dinner is complete you can wander downstairs to the supremely cool (and award winning) Marks Bar for a digestif or an eccentric cocktail.</p>\r\n<p class="p2">This is a top class eatery and would be an ideal location to take your best clients to really spoil them.</p>', 'HIX Soho', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'hix-soho', '', '', '2015-12-11 14:27:01', '2015-12-11 14:27:01', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8888/mct-wordpress/?post_type=maplist&#038;p=93', 0, 'maplist', '', 0),
(94, 1, '2015-10-11 09:30:47', '2015-10-11 09:30:47', '<p class="p1">Situated at the heart of London\'s creative hub, The Hospital club offers a community feel for fellow creatives.<span class="Apple-converted-space">  </span>Their 7 floor venue boasts hotel<span class="Apple-converted-space">  </span>rooms, a<span class="Apple-converted-space">  </span>TV studio,<span class="Apple-converted-space">  </span>multiple screening rooms,<span class="Apple-converted-space">  </span>performance spaces<span class="Apple-converted-space">  </span>as well as<span class="Apple-converted-space">  </span>a lounge bar &amp; restaurant.</p>\r\n<p class="p1">The Hospital Club is extremely popular with media types and is for private members only so you need to beg borrow or steal a membership if you want to hang out here. However, once you are in, you’ll never want to leave.</p>', 'Hospital Club', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'hospital-club', '', '', '2015-12-16 16:39:27', '2015-12-16 16:39:27', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8888/mct-wordpress/?post_type=maplist&#038;p=94', 0, 'maplist', '', 0),
(95, 1, '2015-10-11 09:36:34', '2015-10-11 09:36:34', '<p class="p1">With a perfect spot in the heart of Spitalfields, HotBox is now has a permanent residency. Serving some of the best smoked delights in the capital, from ribs to pulled port and sausages this super cool venue is filled with lively Londoners who want to enjoy top notch BBQ food. Their drinks menu is inspired by the food and offers a host of fun bourbon based cocktails.</p>\r\n<p class="p1">The staff at Hot box are some of the nicest you will come across and with a buzzing atmosphere, and delicious grub – this restaurant it hot hot hot.</p>', 'Hotbox', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'hotbox', '', '', '2015-12-16 16:14:20', '2015-12-16 16:14:20', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8888/mct-wordpress/?post_type=maplist&#038;p=95', 0, 'maplist', '', 0),
(96, 1, '2015-10-11 09:44:11', '2015-10-11 09:44:11', '<p class="p1">Be transported to a 70\'s Parisian den as you peel back the heavy velvet drapes and take in the atmosphere of this happening music hangout.</p>\r\n<p class="p1">Jamboree, established in 2009 is unlike any other bar in London. Filled an eclectic mix of people from all walks of life, anyone who is anyone is welcome and you will be instantly accepted into this unique community.</p>\r\n<p class="p1">Every night presents a different style of music, from Jazz, Gypsy Stomp, Rock n Roll to swing. You will be up on your feet swaying to the music in no time at all – especially if you sample the absinth which is available. The perfect place the creative, that craves something different.</p>', 'Jamboree', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'jamboree', '', '', '2015-12-16 15:39:15', '2015-12-16 15:39:15', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8888/mct-wordpress/?post_type=maplist&#038;p=96', 0, 'maplist', '', 0),
(97, 1, '2015-10-11 09:48:51', '2015-10-11 09:48:51', '<p class="p1">One of London\'s most popular Korean restaurants with celebrity chef<span class="Apple-converted-space">  </span>Judy Joo at the helm,<span class="Apple-converted-space">  </span>JinJuu has been an instant hit. Situated in the very cool Carnaby Street JinJuu serves a range of different fun and casual dining concepts.</p>\r\n<p class="p1">A particular highlight of their menu is their “Anju” selection – which refers to food that you eat while you drink – so picture tacos, sliders and our and sharing platters all with a modern Korean/ Asian fusion.</p>\r\n<p class="p1">The main dining room has an open kitchen and Korean graffiti artwork provides a real treat for the eye, or for a more casual dining experience sit in the bar where on selected evenings their resident DJ transforms JinJuu into a really vibrant venue.</p>', 'JinJuu', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'jinjuu', '', '', '2015-12-16 15:28:03', '2015-12-16 15:28:03', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8888/mct-wordpress/?post_type=maplist&#038;p=97', 0, 'maplist', '', 0) ;
