(98, 1, '2015-10-11 09:56:33', '2015-10-11 09:56:33', '<p class="p1">Nightjar is like a time machine dedicated to the speakeasy culture through the ages. Hidden behind a dark, unlit door way, Night jar is an underground cocktail bar close to Old Street Station.</p>\r\n<p class="p1">They have marvellous live music every night (mostly jazz or blues) and the place gives a real intimate feel with low level lighting and cosy tables.</p>\r\n<p class="p1">Their cocktail menu is playful and divided into historical eras (pre-Prohibition, post-war etc) and each is presented in a weird and wonderful way. Their jugs of cocktails are also a brilliant way to get you and your creative pals in the mood.</p>', 'Nightjar', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'night-jar', '', '', '2015-12-16 14:54:02', '2015-12-16 14:54:02', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8888/mct-wordpress/?post_type=maplist&#038;p=98', 0, 'maplist', '', 0),
(99, 1, '2015-10-11 10:01:08', '2015-10-11 10:01:08', '<p class="p1">Cycling and coffee - who knew the two went together so well? Look Mum no hands has taken the Southbank by storm. A relaxed café serving food and drinks with a fully functioning workshop with mechanic for bike repairs and maintenance- makes this a huge hit with creative across London who cycle to work.</p>\r\n<p class="p1">A real relaxed atmosphere – unlike many coffee shops across London, sit and enjoy a good cup of coffee made from real baristas who take pride in making perfect hot beverage.</p>\r\n<p class="p1">Even if bicycles are not your thing, it is still a buzzing pit stop to meet friends and they also host lots of other fun events from r events from speed dating to knitting classes.</p>', 'Look Mum no Hands', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'look-mum-no-hands', '', '', '2015-12-16 14:29:35', '2015-12-16 14:29:35', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8888/mct-wordpress/?post_type=maplist&#038;p=99', 0, 'maplist', '', 0),
(100, 1, '2015-10-11 10:05:33', '2015-10-11 10:05:33', '<p class="p1">Hidden below Soho\'s best Mexican restaurant &amp; late night venue is a secret cocktail bar, that is \'loco\' about Tequila. It\'s a members only policy (however you can join The Pink Chihuahua club fairly easiy) so you can expect to mingle with only \'the MOST fun\' people in London.</p>\r\n<p class="p1">If you can make it down the ladder-like staircase successfully you are in for a fun filled nighta. Music is loud and fin and before long you will be dancing on the tables. The ultimate “let your hair down” bar in Soho where no one will roll their eyes if things get wild.</p>', 'The Pink Chihuaha', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'the-pink-chihuaha', '', '', '2015-12-16 14:18:11', '2015-12-16 14:18:11', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8888/mct-wordpress/?post_type=maplist&#038;p=100', 0, 'maplist', '', 0),
(101, 1, '2015-10-11 10:11:58', '2015-10-11 10:11:58', '<p class="p1">The Portside Parlour is an authentic underground Rum bar hidden away in East London, as long as you are not put off by entering through a toilet. The quirky cubicle door way, asks you to “flush to enter” and once you do you will be welcomed into a candle-lit cocktail bar with a nautical vibe.</p>\r\n<p class="p1">Sink into the soft leather sofas and sip their ridiculously good list cocktails, and over 50 different types of rum to ensure all your stresses sail away.</p>\r\n<p class="p1">This hangout was only meant to be a short-term popup but due to popular demand has had its residency extended so make sure you go and share the love so this gem stays for longer.</p>', 'Portside Parlour', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'portside-parlour', '', '', '2015-12-16 14:14:52', '2015-12-16 14:14:52', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8888/mct-wordpress/?post_type=maplist&#038;p=101', 0, 'maplist', '', 0),
(102, 1, '2015-10-11 10:15:32', '2015-10-11 10:15:32', '<p class="p1">A multi-sensory delight, this 1920\'s cocktail bar uses smells, fogs and foams to create incredible drinking experience unlike any other.</p>\r\n<p class="p1">Designed with a classic speakeasy vibe, Purl has a stunning baroque interior mixed with beautiful vintage accessories.</p>\r\n<p class="p1">Prepare to be wowed by the bartenders are extremely talent and unorthodox mixology, this is really a place to take your friends or colleagues who you want to impress.</p>', 'PURL', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'purl', '', '', '2015-12-15 16:43:15', '2015-12-15 16:43:15', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8888/mct-wordpress/?post_type=maplist&#038;p=102', 0, 'maplist', '', 0),
(103, 1, '2015-10-11 10:17:57', '2015-10-11 10:17:57', '<p class="p1">A handsome Victorian pub with a trendy Smithfield edge The Old Red Cow is one of London’s oldest public houses. Steeped in history the inside is filled with worn wood but teamed with twinkling chandeliers and a very popular juke box it is the perfect mix of old and new.</p>\r\n<p class="p1">They boast one of their largest selection of craft beer in London from dark, light, wheat, Belgian and even fruit ales available. The menu serves classic pub food – don’t go if you are expecting a gastro pub, but it is of a high standard and they are famed for their Sunday roast!</p>\r\n<p class="p1">Ideal hangout for creatives who need to kick back at the weekend and escape the rat race in this old school cosy pub.</p>', 'The Old Red Cow', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'the-old-red-cow', '', '', '2015-12-15 16:14:42', '2015-12-15 16:14:42', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8888/mct-wordpress/?post_type=maplist&#038;p=103', 0, 'maplist', '', 0),
(104, 1, '2015-10-11 10:38:03', '2015-10-11 10:38:03', '<p class="p1">An award-winning<span class="Apple-converted-space">  </span>bar and lounge that sits comfortably below one of the famous ROKA restaurants in Charlotte Street, Soho. This stylish restaurant bar, is so much more than a warm up act for it\'s upstairs diners, at Shōchū you can sample the Japanese robatayaki cuisine and sip wonderful cocktails in the striking yet comfortable surroundings.<span class="Apple-converted-space">  </span>Its spot is ideal for creatives needing a quick escape from a mad day, where you can unwind in this central yet secluded space.</p>', 'Shōchū Lounge', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'shochu-lounge', '', '', '2015-12-15 15:33:11', '2015-12-15 15:33:11', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8888/mct-wordpress/?post_type=maplist&#038;p=104', 0, 'maplist', '', 0),
(105, 1, '2015-10-11 10:54:30', '2015-10-11 10:54:30', '<p class="p1">One of Denmark’s most popular restaurants have exported their menu to London!<span class="Apple-converted-space">  </span>Serving high-quality, fresh food based on a unique combination of traditional sushi and yakitori sticks from the grill – it is surprising what an incredible infusion it creates.</p>\r\n<p class="p1">The Sticks n Sushi menu presents a host of rich flavours from rib eye steak marinated in Japanese BBQ sauces to pork sticks in a wasabi and ceaser dressing. Japanese restaurants are fast becoming the most popular style of restaurant in London but Sticks n Sushi defiantly rivals the leading establishments.</p>\r\n<p class="p1">Ideal for the creatives who wants to eat the best of Japanese in Scandanvian chic hangout , at a reasonable price.</p>', 'Sticks\'n \'Sushi', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'sticksn-sushi', '', '', '2015-12-15 14:55:57', '2015-12-15 14:55:57', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8888/mct-wordpress/?post_type=maplist&#038;p=105', 0, 'maplist', '', 0),
(106, 1, '2015-10-11 10:58:13', '2015-10-11 10:58:13', '<p class="p1">You are instantly transported to stunning café in central Europe as you enter the Wolseley. With incredibly Grand décor, this Grade II listed building is popular with everyone from celebrities to trendy media types.</p>\r\n<p class="p1">The menu is exquisite and sits somewhere between British, French and Austrian cuisines and the drinks offering is extensive.</p>\r\n<p class="p1">The Wolseley set the benchmark for graceful metropolitan dining and with attentive staff who make everyone feel like special guest, it is the place to go to feel a real sense of occasion and is great for people watching.</p>', 'Wolseley', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'wolseley', '', '', '2015-12-09 17:11:31', '2015-12-09 17:11:31', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8888/mct-wordpress/?post_type=maplist&#038;p=106', 0, 'maplist', '', 0),
(107, 1, '2015-10-11 11:00:59', '2015-10-11 11:00:59', '<p class="p1">Sitting in central creative territory (Clerkenwell) – Zetter Townhouse is the ultimate hangout. An award winning cocktail bar with a stunning mix of antique Georgian furniture (and the odd stuffed animal) creates a cosy ambiance. Their cocktail menu is small but the list was created by Tony Conigliaro famed for his experimental techniques with ingredients so each one is crafted with care.</p>\r\n<p class="p1">Zetter Townhouse also offers accommodation in the style of a gorgeous 13 bedroom townhouse which makes it’s guests feel like they are staying in a private residence of an eccentric star rather than a hotel!</p>', 'Zetter Townhouse', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'zetter-townhouse', '', '', '2015-12-09 16:50:45', '2015-12-09 16:50:45', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8888/mct-wordpress/?post_type=maplist&#038;p=107', 0, 'maplist', '', 0),
(109, 2, '2015-10-11 18:20:12', '2015-10-11 18:20:12', '<p class="p2">Business is done better on a full stomach. Everyone loves a good client lunch – an opportunity to charm your way to that hot bit of business. Choosing the venue for the client lunch is highly important – you need to have the right balance of formality but with a relaxed edge; you want it to be buzzy but not too busy, you want them to feel schmoozed but not like you are trying to hard.</p>\r\n<p class="p2">So we’ve created a full proof list of the best client lunch venues which will ensure you get the deal done:</p>\r\n<p class="p2"><b>The Clove Club</b></p>\r\n<p class="p2">For East London excellence there is one place that stands out. The Clove Club is a gem situated in the amazing building of Shoreditch Town Hall. They specialise in classic cuisine from British sourced ingredients and with an ambitious menu you’ll want to sample every dish. A cool relaxed, table cloth free restaurant will put your clients instantly at ease, leaving you the simple task of enjoying the food and winning their business.</p>\r\n<p class="p2"><b>Bob Bob Ricard</b></p>\r\n<p class="p2">In the heart of Soho Bob Bob Ricard remains one of the front runners for creatives to wine and dine their best clients. This Russian/English mixed menu offers good wholesome food with a little extra pizazz. The décor is impressive and the booths cosy, and despite the “elegant” dress code that staff are not very hot on it and couldn’t be more welcoming. A lovely vibe at lunchtime as the atmosphere builds around you, leaving your clients quietly impressed with your choice of venue.</p>\r\n<p class="p2"><b>Hush </b></p>\r\n<p class="p2">You may exclude Mayfair from you shortlist, deeming it too posh for a creative client lunch, however hidden away in a courtyard in the centre of Mayfair sits Hush - an informal brasserie that has been on the map for over 15 years. Sample their selection of iced teas and their award winning burgers. Or if your palette is feeling a little more fancy, you can enjoy their speciality cocktails and nibble on steak tartar on sourdough toast. The staff are extremely attentive and will allow you to eat and chat at your leisure, so you can sit back relax and schmooze your client.</p>\r\n<p class="p2"><b>Grill on the market </b></p>\r\n<p class="p2">With the rise of agencies and studios in Farringdon, Clerkenwell is a spot hugely popular with creative start-ups and Smithfield has also seen a huge revival. Grill on the Market is a no-nonsense, wholesome food in a ultra-cool open plan restaurant. Famed for their 28 day aged steak, you can really wow your clients with this grub – their puddings are pretty spectacular too. A buzzing atmosphere with an edgy vibe – it really is the perfect place for an effortless business lunch.</p>\r\n<p class="p1"><b>Beach Blanket Babylon </b></p>\r\n<p class="p1">Established since the 1990s BBB as it is often known is probably the Queen of the client lunch. Impressive stature, this Georgian Mansion is transformed into an ultra-stylish bohemian chic bar and restaurant (and if you get a little carried away, a night club too). Ease your clients into the meet with a signature cocktail and then schmooze them with a delicious chateaubriand or crispy duck. An amazing vibe day and night in this Notting Hill hang out guaranteed to bowl over your client.</p>\r\n<p class="p1"></p>', 'Top 5 client lunch spots', 'Business is done better on a full stomach, everyone loves a good client lunch', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'top-5-client-lunch-spots-london', '', '', '2015-12-16 13:34:52', '2015-12-16 13:34:52', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8888/mct-wordpress/?p=109', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(110, 1, '2015-10-11 18:20:12', '2015-10-11 18:20:12', '<strong>Lorem Ipsum</strong> is simply dummy text of the printing and typesetting industry. Lorem Ipsum has been the industry\'s standard dummy text ever since the 1500s, when an unknown printer took a galley of type and scrambled it to make a type specimen book. It has survived not only five centuries, but also the leap into electronic typesetting, remaining essentially unchanged. It was popularised in the 1960s with the release of Letraset sheets containing Lorem Ipsum passages, and more recently with desktop publishing software like Aldus PageMaker including versions of Lorem Ipsum.', 'Post2', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '109-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-10-11 18:20:12', '2015-10-11 18:20:12', '', 109, 'http://localhost:8888/mct-wordpress/2015/10/11/109-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(111, 4, '2015-10-11 18:20:20', '2015-10-11 18:20:20', '<p class="p2"><b>Electric Cinema : Review </b></p>\r\n<p class="p2">As Office Manager for a creative recruitment consultancy I am often on the lookout for cool, creative venues to host internal and external events.</p>\r\n<p class="p2">I am a massive fan of the cinema. I go at least every fortnight! Normally I head to the VUE cinema as it’s close to our offices in Angel, but last month my colleague and I headed to Electric Cinema in Shoreditch. I had been to the venue a few times for our End of Year meeting presentations – its the perfect venue to get the company together for a presentation and roundup of the year. I had not however been to watch a film there.</p>\r\n<p class="p2">We headed down to the cinema after work and walked the short distance from Liverpool Street Station. We’d booked out tickets on line prior to our arrival so entry was super easy. There is a bar upstairs so we managed to grab a beer and a glass of wine first and ordered a second round of refreshments to take down stairs to the screening. As a regular cinema goer, popcorn is a MUST and I have to say, the fresh popcorn served at the Electric Cinema is top notch!</p>\r\n<p class="p2">Our seats were perfect – the centre of the second row, but with 50 seats and huge screen, I doubt any seats are bad? We sank down into the velvet sofas and snuggled under the blankets provided for a real “home movie” feel.</p>\r\n<p class="p2">The film was brilliant – a comedy called Train Wreck starring Amy Schumer which I Loved – but more than the film, I loved the atmosphere and vibe at this really cool cinema</p>\r\n<p class="p2">While the cost is more than my usual high-street cinema, it is worth it and I will be returning very soon. I would also highly recommend the venue, for hire if you need somewhere to host screening or private events, especially within the creative industry – it’s ideal.</p>\r\n<p class="p2">- Lauren McGee.</p>', 'Electric cinema', 'Velvet sofas and snuggled under the blankets provided for a real “home movie” feel', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'electric-cinema', '', '', '2015-12-16 13:34:26', '2015-12-16 13:34:26', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8888/mct-wordpress/?p=111', 0, 'post', '', 0),
