(212, 1, '2015-10-16 11:07:21', '2015-10-16 11:07:21', '<p class="p2">Despite kindles seemingly taking over the world, there are some of us who still desperately cling onto our hard-backs, who adore the turning of paper pages of good old fashioned book. But while many are downloading the latest copy of the new “hot read” there are a still a lot of die-hard book fans mooching around beautiful bookshops across the capital.</p>\r\n<p class="p2"><b>The Society Club, Soho </b></p>\r\n<p class="p2">Dispelling the common opinion that book people can be bland, The Society Club in London’s Soho proves otherwise.</p>\r\n<p class="p2">A bookstore, come bar, come gallery allows you to wander around some stunning art, grab a beverage from the bar and then find a pew and immerse yourself in a good book. A thoroughly relaxing spot, perfect to unwind at the end of a hard day.</p>\r\n<a href="http://thesocietyclub">thesocietyclub</a> - <a href="https://twitter.com/societyclubsoho">@SocietyClubSoho</a>\r\n<p class="p2"><b>Daunt Books, Marleybone. </b></p>\r\n<p class="p2">Founded back in 1990, a trip to Daunts original book shop in Marylebone will transport you into the Edwardian era. Famed for its travel and leisure literary collection – the books are actually arranged by country, regardless of the nature of the book (fiction, history or novel). An absolute must visit for any true book lover in London.</p>\r\n<p class="p2"><a href="http://www.dauntbooks.co.uk/">dauntbooks</a></p>\r\n<p class="p2"><b>Artwords, Shoredtich </b></p>\r\n<p class="p2">One of the coolest bookshops in London, Artwords is filled with collections of carefully chosen books and quirky titles, positioned on brilliant displays. Best known for their collection of literature on contemporary visual culture, covering fine art, design and fashion it is a must visit for creatives in London.</p>\r\n<p class="p2"><b>Gosh </b></p>\r\n<p class="p2">Oh my gosh, a bookstore dedicated to comics! Industrial-chic, this quirky bookstore stocks the best in graphic storytelling from the most widely read superhero stories to manga and small press titles and many translated European titles. With enthusiastic fun staff, this is place is the ideal hangout for anyone who loves a fantasy read.</p>\r\n<p class="p2"><b>Foyles, Charing Cross. </b></p>\r\n<p class="p2">The opposite of boutique, this flagship book shop has the most incredible collection of over 200,000 across 4 miles of shelves which would excite even mild book fans. Foyles has over 80 booksellers,</p>\r\n<p class="p2">who are always more than happy to offer you help on whatever you may need, so even if you are usually put off by overly commercial bookstores, this one is worth popping along to, for stroll through the collections and top advice from the experts.</p>\r\n<p class="p2"><a href="http://www.foyles.co.uk/bookstore-charing-cross">foyles book shop</a></p>\r\n<p class="p2"></p>', 'Resuscitating the Bookshop', 'Despite kindles seemingly taking over the world, there are some of us who still desperately cling onto our hard-backs, who adore the turning of paper pages of good old fashioned book. But while many are downloading the latest copy of the new “hot read” there are a still a lot of die-hard book fans mooching around beautiful bookshops across the capital.', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '133-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-10-16 11:07:21', '2015-10-16 11:07:21', '', 133, 'http://localhost:8888/mct-wordpress/133-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0) ;
