(281, 1, '2015-10-22 18:00:02', '2015-10-22 18:00:02', '<p class="p1">London has long been known as the “hub” for creative, with it is budding agency life, talented creatives and general buzz, it has always drawn the ‘cool crowd’. The capital now encompasses a full spectrum of creative disciplines, including digital, tech and design, film and TV production, arts and theatre, mobile technology and gaming – and is the location of choice for the world’s leading advertising and digital agencies. Soho, the heart of London was always acknowledged as being there powerhouse of creative but over the past 5 years, Shoreditch, Farringdon, Hammersmith and King’s Cross are now firmly securing their position on the “creative” map.</p>\r\n<p class="p1"></p>\r\n<p class="p1">London is teeming with cool bars, restaurants and pop­ups and we have made it our job to suss out the very best. We teamed up with Purple consultancy, creative recruitment consultancy in London’s Islington, to survey their huge creative audience and find out just where the “cool” kids hangouts. The results were awesome – uncovering unique sites, brand new venues and an array of quirky spots!</p>', 'About us', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '163-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-10-22 18:00:02', '2015-10-22 18:00:02', '', 163, 'http://localhost:8888/mct-wordpress/163-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0) ;
