(633, 2, '2015-12-16 11:42:37', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'We’re all drowning in an ocean of London craft beer. From blondes and stouts to porters and IPAs: craft beer pub’s beer selections are growing daily. But which taprooms are the top rooms? And which alehouses are the failhouses? Which is London’s best craft beer pub?\r\n\r\n<strong>1. The Stormbird</strong>\r\n\r\nDown in the gastro-heaven of Camberwell’s Church Street is the high-flying Stormbird. With 15 perennially changing craft beers (and the occasional cider) on show and half a dozen fridges full of cans and bottles, the beer selection at the Stormbird is unrivalled. The interior finds a charming midpoint between rustic and minimalist. From Partizan to Kernel to Beavertown to obscure specialties brewed in tiny quantities, <a href="http://thestormbirdpub.co.uk/">Stormbird</a> is always stocked with the cream of the crop.\r\n\r\n<strong>2. Euston Tap</strong>\r\n\r\nToo often large train stations signify barren-zones when it comes to good pubs and restaurants, as big chains cramp out indie establishments. The <a href="http://www.eustontap.com/">Euston Tap</a> is a happy exception, allowing Mancunians to grab a quality craft beer the moment they arrive in London. The Tap is small and cosy with a nice garden area unfortunately placed next to the hell-on-Earth wind-tunnel/pollution machine that is Euston Road. Try the tiny upstairs living room for maximum cosiness.\r\n\r\n<strong>3. The Sebright Arms</strong>\r\n\r\nA notorious muso hangout spot, <a href="http://www.sebrightarms.co.uk/">The Sebright Arms</a> is also a champion of stalwart craft ales and indie brewers. Like any good London craft beer pub, the labels here are in a constant state of excitable flux, but expect to see a lot of Brick Brewery, Orbit Beers and Brew By Numbers\r\n\r\n<strong>4. OSLO</strong>\r\n\r\nThe <a href="http://www.mothclub.co.uk/">Moth Club</a> of 2013, <a href="http://www.oslohackney.com/">OSLO</a> quickly become recognized as one of Hackney’s coolest venues after a quick-fire series of amazing gigs and delicious menus. Their learned beer selection has been critical in that success as they champion obscure, deserving brews that always deliver. You can find Kona Big Wave here on tap. Enough said.\r\n\r\n<strong>5.The Chelsea Pensioner</strong>\r\n\r\nIt’s not all East you know. As everyone knows, the established Ladies and Gentlemen of West London were downing real ale on the side of the Thames when Nathan Barley was still wearing Pampers. Fulham’s <a href="http://www.thechelseapensioner.co.uk/">Chelsea Pensioner</a> is a haven of real ale, craft beers and dry, flat ciders that would make a Somerset farmer go “oh arr”. Watch out on match days if you’re not a blue.', 'London’s Best Craft Beer Pubs', '', 'draft', 'open', 'open', '', '', '', '', '2015-12-16 11:42:37', '2015-12-16 11:42:37', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8888/mct-wordpress/?p=633', 0, 'post', '', 0),
