(635, 5, '2015-12-16 11:48:42', '2015-12-16 11:48:42', 'Meeting people in the great social metropolis of London is easy enough. People watching is more fun, though. Here are the capital’s best people watching spots for creatives.\r\n\r\n<strong>1. Ace Hotel, Shoreditch</strong>\r\n\r\nIt had to be Ace, didn’t it? Walk into the basement of this post-hipster joint and you’ll feel the clientele look up from their overpriced MacBooks and analyse you. Intimidating? Yes. Now, sit yourself down, take out your MacBook and become one of the people-watching crowd. Whether you’re in the café and facing out onto Shoreditch High Street, or you’re in the restaurant in the belly of the beast, <a href="http://www.acehotel.com/london">Ace Hotel</a> in Shoreditch is one of the great people-watching institutions of London.\r\n\r\n<strong>2. The Craft Beer Co, Brixton </strong>\r\n\r\nJump on the Viccy line and head south to Brixton. This <a href="http://thecraftbeerco.com/pubs/brixton/">cosy little craft beer bar</a> tucked away behind Brixton train station is one of six in London, but the Brixton branch is definitely the best spot for an afternoon of people watching. Pick a stool looking out of the window and watch the street market workers do their thing.\r\n\r\n<strong>3. South Bank</strong>\r\n\r\nWe couldn’t choose one specific thing about London’s South Bank above the others. From the Haywood Gallery, to the Royal Festival Hall and everything in between, park yourself on a bench and watch the world go by.\r\n\r\n<strong>4. Campus London</strong>\r\n\r\nThis is Google’s hub for creatives in London. The people there are well-known for their collective entrepreneurial-ness… and their love for strong coffee (it’s probably a flat white…). If you want people watching in London where you might actually learn something, <a href="https://www.campus.co/">Campus London</a> is the place to be. <strong> </strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>5. </strong><strong>Ronnie Scott’s Jazz Club</strong>\r\n\r\nWe had to put <a href="http://www.ronniescotts.co.uk/">Ronnie Scott’s</a> on the list. With over 55 years of history, this word-famous jazz spot is one of the oldest in the world. Perfect for entertaining clients or a solitary evening of people-watching, sit yourself in a smoky, atmosphere-soaked corner and take in the sites.', 'Prime People Watching Spots in London', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'prime-people-watching-spots-in-london', '', '', '2015-12-16 13:34:05', '2015-12-16 13:34:05', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8888/mct-wordpress/?p=635', 0, 'post', '', 0),
