(638, 5, '2015-12-16 13:33:21', '2015-12-16 13:33:21', 'Is the Northern line getting you down again? We don’t blame you. It’s a hot, sweaty nightmare. What you need are some ways to de-stress in London. Here are five.\r\n\r\n<strong>1. Rave It up at Morning Gloryville </strong>\r\n\r\nProbably not what you think it is, <a href="http://morninggloryville.com/">Morning Gloryville</a> is an early-morning, alcohol-free rave that gets you up, out of bed and dancing to phat beatz all before work. It’s an actual <em>scientific fact</em> that exercise helps you de-stress and you might meet new some new, none-stressful friends whilst you’re at it.\r\n\r\n<strong>2. De-stress at the Sky Garden</strong>\r\n\r\nNot just a swanky bar at the top of one of London’s tallest towers, <a href="http://skygarden.london/sky-garden">The Sky Garden</a> is literally that: a garden in the sky. Walk out from the elevator (following quite a vigorous frisk!), grab your flute of champagne and take a seat amongst the foliage. Let all your fears, troubles and concerns melt away as you stare out over the capital.\r\n\r\n<strong>3. Frank’s Café</strong>\r\n\r\nIf you’re a South Londoner (and let’s be real, as creatives, many of us are…), you simply need to tick <a href="http://frankscafe.org.uk/">Frank’s Café</a> off your bucket list before the inevitable move to Islington. It’s a bar/art space on top of a multi-story carpark in Peckham that overlooks the whole of London. With genuinely breath-taking views, beautiful drinks, and even more beautiful people, you’ll be feeling chilled in no time.\r\n\r\n<strong>4. Restore Yourself with Restorative Yoga</strong>\r\n\r\nRight at the heart of trendy Bethnal Green is <a href="http://www.yogaplace.co.uk/">Yoga Place</a>, a beautifully designed relaxation space dedicated to the art of restorative yoga. Man, woman, beginner or expert, everybody’s a winner at Yoga Place. Along with classes and courses, weekend workshops and holistic therapy sessions take place all year-round. This is de-stressing for the serious student of the art of calm.\r\n\r\n<strong>5. Purrrfect Calm at Lady Dinah’s Cat Emporium</strong>\r\n\r\nAnimals are great. We can all agree on that. London is now the official home of animal cafes and in this case, the original is the best. <a href="http://ladydinahs.com/">Lady Dinah’s Cat Emporium</a> is a fantastic place for a spot of afternoon tea, alongside the company of your favorite feline friends. Stroke, pet and feel the pressures of the outside word melt away.', 'Where to De-stress in London', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'where-to-de-stress-in-london', '', '', '2015-12-18 11:18:04', '2015-12-18 11:18:04', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8888/mct-wordpress/?p=638', 0, 'post', '', 0),
